wer</span><hr size=1> Later this year, Verant Interactive (VI) in association with Sony Online Entertainment (SOE) will be releasing the newest expansion to their widely popular Massively Multiplayer Online Role-playing Game (MMPORG) Everquest (EQ).   This expansion will be called Planes of Power (PoP).  This expansion will offer a number of new planes in order to engage all of the current players and in the hopes of enticing new players into the game.<br><br>We have had the opportunity to take a peek behind the scenes at VI, to take a peek at some of the new content and zones in PoP.<br><br>There are many new planar zones in PoP.  The first and most widely known about at this point is the Plane of Tranquility (PoT).  When on PoT, one can expect a feeling of uncontrolled giddiness, and laughter from nowhere.  There are many places where one can sit and look at a wall if they so desire.  While on PoT you will not be able to fight or duel, as on PoT you should be too happy to fight anyone.   There are also many food vendors on PoT who understand the pangs of hunger you’ll feel, and they sell PoT food, that you can munch while you’re on PoT but when you leave you find it’s mysteriously gone, and wonder where it went.<br><br>The next plane we had the honor of seeing was the Plane of Sin (PoS).  This PoS was not yet skinned or mostly coded, but they were alpha testing it anyway.  When you zone in to PoS there is a random bug that will drop you under the world, killing you and then drop your corpse at some random location within the zone so that a GM won’t help you.  We interviewed one of the designers of PoS who had this to say, “We had originally thought of an elaborate design involving half naked elves, and whore houses of ogres, but due to the strict enforcement buy the rating associations, PoS has become the PoS that it is today.  We feel that the sin in this PoS is that people will be angered, and they should be angered by sin.  This PoS is non-offensive to anyone except the player, who should be offended.”<br><br>These were the only two zones we were privy to as the tour guide saw us taking notes and wanted to confiscate our notepad.  Eventually, when our budget increases, we will get an exclusive on the PoP expansion.  Until then, enjoy the juicy tidbits we have today.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><HTML><body><img src="http://www.lvcm.com/darkelf/sig.jpg"> <br></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ueqwolfran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQWolfran</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.seaforthlanding.com/images/misc/doom_anm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#33cc33>Drinalite</font></span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 1:56:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2693.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.seaforthlanding.com/images/misc/shaman.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sneak peek at Planes of Power</span><hr size=1> I hate April fools jokes..<br><br>Especially when they're posted on April 2nd <p><br>---<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126557" target="wolfran">Me</a> / <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126564" target="alt">Twink</a><br><br><b>"Hanlon's Razor:</b><br>Never attribute to malice that which is adequately expl